 mutual giant component of susceptible individuals,\nwhich is crucial to keep the functionality of the system. In addition, we find\nthat for relatively small values of the overlap $q$, social distancing policies\nmight not be needed at all to maintain the functionality of the system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Apr 2020 14:32:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Aug 2020 20:15:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 26 Aug 2020 16:10:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-27"}
